    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Log form submissions with Google Sheets and Gmail and log the results\n\n**Pattern:** Form Intake · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Form\n\n## What it does\nLog form submissions with Google Sheets and Gmail and log the results. It starts from a hosted form submission.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual routing is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nNew Lead Form Submission → Required Fields Present? → Prepare Approval Packet → Request Approval via Slack → Hold for Decision → Approved? → Execute Approved Action (API) → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to form intake without manual effort\n- Anyone automating routing in sales\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Improves response time\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "59284211-ffde-09fc-f479-98255f588ba4",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "286bf456-217f-14ae-ea7b-6ca7c22dc04b",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "0d5c97e0-e629-fd13-44ef-ca6a25233024",
      "name": "⏱ Rate limiting"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🙋 Human in the loop\n\nThe workflow pauses at the Wait node until a human posts a decision to the resume URL (included in the approval message). Approve → the action executes; anything else → recorded as declined. No timeout is set by default — add one under the Wait node's options if approvals go stale.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        610,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "3b2e2bcf-192a-143d-d31d-985474a215fd",
      "name": "🙋 Human in the loop"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your routing process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1030,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "831952b0-44d1-41fd-2e8f-0993b00aa27d",
      "name": "🛠 Customize me"
    }
